    "summary": "Probing questions before calling final positions",
    "content": "I hear you've both converged on Variant D. Before I call for final positions, I want to make sure the real trade-offs have been aired. A few pointed questions:\n\n1. Did you seriously consider Variant A's advantage of enabling future field-level diffs? Or did you dismiss it too quickly as YAGNI?\n2. The canonical serialization dependency in Variant D — are you comfortable that Jackson configuration changes or Kotlin class refactors won't silently break hash stability? The user said false positives are acceptable, but \"acceptable\" and \"good\" are different things.\n3. Where exactly should the 4 hashes live — on SaasConfigData itself (computed at save-time) or on ConfigActivation (computed at activation-time)? This matters for correctness.\n\nPush back on the architect if they're over-engineering the implementation. But also tell me honestly: is there anything about Variant A that Variant D genuinely cannot do?"
  }
}

